PrecisDecision to UPHOLD a ruling made by the Canadian Transportation Agency (Decision 706-R-1999) with respect to a complaint filed by the VILLAGE OF WOOD MOUNTAIN as to whether or not the Canadian Pacific Railway Company complied with the Canada Transportation Act when it ceased operations on its Wood Mountain Subdivision in Saskatchewan.

precis:
Decision to UPHOLD a ruling made by the Canadian Transportation Agency
(Decision 706-R-1999) with respect to a complaint filed by the VILLAGE OF
WOOD MOUNTAIN as to whether or not the Canadian Pacific Railway Company
complied with the Canada Transportation Act when it ceased operations on
its Wood Mountain Subdivision in Saskatchewan.
